Paper Moon is a 1973 American comedy-drama film directed by Peter Bogdanovich and released by Paramount Pictures .
Screenwriter Alvin Sargent adapted the script from the novel Addie Pray by Joe David Brown .
The film , shot in black-and-white , is set in Kansas and Missouri during the Great Depression .
It stars the real-life father and daughter pairing of Ryan and Tatum O'Neal as protagonists Moze and Addie .